  "prompt": "My pet cat scratched me accidentally.Its not vaccinated and I'm from India. 7 days have passed but the cat is fully well. Do I need anti-rabies shots?",
  "response": "Rabies is a serious and potentially fatal illness, and it is important to be cautious with any potential exposure. In India, rabies is present, and animal bites or scratches from unvaccinated pets are a cause for concern. \n\nIf your cat is healthy and shows no signs of rabies after 7 days, the likelihood that your cat has rabies is low. However, rabies can have an incubation period in animals during which they may not show symptoms.\n\nIt is advisable to consult a healthcare professional for a thorough assessment and guidance. They may recommend providing post-exposure prophylaxis (PEP) to ensure your safety. Remember, rabies is almost always fatal once symptoms appear, so taking precautionary measures is critical.\n\nFor future safety, vaccinating your pet against rabies and keeping its vaccinations up to date is important.",
